<TITLE> Italian journalist dies after Paris mugging </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 PARIS, Aug 15 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - An Italian sports journalist died in a Paris hospital from a serious head injury suffered when he was mugged at a Paris metro station, police said on Wednesday. Sergio Vantaggiato, 40, who was pronounced brain dead shortly after his admission to St. Louis Hospital on Sunday, was officially declared dead at 2155 GMT on Tuesday, a police official said. Police are hunting two men who snatched the Italian's back pack at the Bir-Hakeim metro station near the Eiffel Tower. Vantaggiato, who worked for the private TeleRama network, caught up with one of his attackers after a chase but fell during the ensuing struggle, suffering a serious head injury. Aides to French Prime Minister Francois Fillon said on Tuesday he had called the journalist's family and his Italian counterpart Romano Prodi to express his sadness over the atta
